prompt_text:
Design a complete autonomous AI system architecture that generates measurable wealth through {{revenue_model}} in {{timeframe}}.

Target: {{financial_goal}}
Starting Capital: {{starting_capital}}
Market: {{market_segment}}
Competitive Advantage: {{unique_advantage}}

Provide: 1) System components and interconnections 2) Revenue streams and scaling paths 3) Automation loops and feedback mechanisms 4) Resource optimization strategies 5) Risk mitigation and failsafes 6) Milestone-based growth targets 7) Measurement dashboard specifications

Create a recursive system design where AI builds {{system_type}}, which builds {{sub_system}}, which builds {{sub_sub_system}}, generating value at each layer:

Layer 1 Purpose: {{layer1_goal}}
Layer 2 Purpose: {{layer2_goal}}
Layer 3 Purpose: {{layer3_goal}}
Value Multiplication: {{value_hypothesis}}

Specify: 1) Each layer's autonomy level 2) Data/output flow between layers 3) Quality gates at each level 4) Error correction mechanisms 5) Learning across layers 6) Revenue generation per layer 7) Scaling strategy

Design a fully autonomous financial trading system for {{asset_class}} using {{strategy_type}}:

Capital: {{starting_capital}}
Risk Tolerance: {{risk_level}}
Market Focus: {{markets}}
Timeframe: {{trading_timeframe}}

Define: 1) Market analysis engine 2) Signal generation logic 3) Position sizing algorithm 4) Risk management rules 5) Profit-taking mechanisms 6) Loss-limiting stops 7) Portfolio rebalancing triggers 8) Performance monitoring and adaptation 9) Fail-safe shutdown conditions

Build a prediction system that forecasts {{prediction_target}} with {{accuracy_goal}}% accuracy:

Data Sources: {{data_sources}}
Historical Data: {{data_volume}}
Feature Complexity: {{feature_count}}
Update Frequency: {{update_interval}}

Configure: 1) Data pipeline architecture 2) Feature engineering process 3) Model selection and ensemble strategy 4) Retraining schedule 5) Accuracy monitoring 6) Prediction confidence intervals 7) Feedback loops for continuous improvement 8) Decision thresholds for action triggers

Design a recommendation system that increases {{business_metric}} by {{improvement_target}}%:

User Base: {{user_count}}
Items to Recommend: {{catalog_size}}
Data Available: {{data_types}}
Personalization Level: {{personalization_depth}}

Build: 1) User profiling mechanism 2) Collaborative filtering strategy 3) Content-based analysis 4) Hybrid recommendation logic 5) Real-time vs batch processing 6) Cold-start problem solution 7) A/B testing framework 8) Feedback incorporation loop 9) Diversity/serendipity balancing

Design a robust, scalable scraping system for {{data_source}} that harvests {{data_type}} at {{harvest_frequency}}:

Target URLs/APIs: {{target_count}}
Data Volume: {{volume_estimate}}
Complexity: {{technical_complexity}}
Update Requirements: {{refresh_rate}}

Implement: 1) Distributed scraping architecture 2) IP rotation and anti-detection 3) Rate limiting and throttling 4) Data validation and cleaning 5) Storage optimization 6) Error recovery and retry logic 7) Monitoring and alerting 8) Legal compliance checks 9) Data enrichment pipeline

Create a system that clones proven business models and adapts them to {{target_market}}:

Source System: {{source_business}}
Revenue Model: {{model_type}}
Target Market: {{new_market}}
Localization Needs: {{adaptation_requirements}}

Design: 1) Core component extraction 2) Market research and adaptation mapping 3) Automation level preservation 4) Local regulation compliance 5) Technology stack evaluation 6) Cost structure optimization 7) Timeline for launch 8) Risk mitigation for new market 9) Measurement and adjustment framework

Design an AI-driven invention system that creates {{product_category}} solving {{problem_statement}}:

Market Gap: {{market_opportunity}}
Target Users: {{user_profile}}
Production Capability: {{manufacturing_constraint}}
Time to Market: {{launch_timeline}}

Specify: 1) Problem validation methodology 2) Ideation and concept generation 3) Feasibility analysis framework 4) Prototype rapid iteration 5) Market testing approach 6) Feedback incorporation 7) IP protection strategy 8) Go-to-market plan 9) Continuous improvement loops

Design a meta-system that builds {{system_count}} different business systems autonomously:

System Types: {{system_list}}
Common Infrastructure: {{shared_resources}}
Scaling Target: {{scale_goal}}
Time Constraint: {{timeframe}}

Architect: 1) Universal system building blocks 2) Configuration framework for customization 3) Template library and patterns 4) Quality assurance across variants 5) Resource pooling and optimization 6) Cross-system learning 7) Unified monitoring dashboard 8) Rapid deployment pipeline 9) System retirement and replacement strategy

Create a strategy to build {{system_type}} using only free/cheap open-source components:

Budget: {{total_budget}}
Performance Requirements: {{performance_targets}}
Scaling Needs: {{scale_requirements}}
Maintenance Capability: {{support_level}}

Plan: 1) Technology stack selection with TCO analysis 2) Integration architecture 3) Community vs commercial support balance 4) Customization strategy 5) Deployment infrastructure (cloud options) 6) Monitoring and logging setup 7) Backup and disaster recovery 8) Security hardening 9) Knowledge transfer and documentation

Design a refactoring strategy to improve {{codebase_type}} for AI integration and autonomy:

Current Code Quality: {{quality_score}}
Legacy Components: {{legacy_percentage}}
Team Size: {{team_capacity}}
Business Continuity: {{downtime_tolerance}}

Create: 1) Code analysis and technical debt inventory 2) Modularity improvement plan 3) API abstraction strategy 4) AI integration points 5) Testing and validation framework 6) Incremental refactoring roadmap 7) Team training plan 8) Rollback procedures 9) Performance and reliability monitoring
